race.description: The Man Walk Australia Maiden Plate
race.comment: CHISPA (11) raced handy and found plenty under pressure but missed by half a length on debut last start over 1200m at the Beaumont track. Bred to stay so any extra distance is a plus. Sure to be in the finish. TAHURANGI (14) continues to race well deep into this first campaign. Ran on well to be beaten less than a length last time out over this course and distance. Perfectly drawn and should be thereabouts again. The consistent EL QASABI (1) closed well to get up for second over 1200m at Wyong at his latest appearance. New to this trip but it looks the right option. BUGATTE (4) returned with a decent effort at the Beaumont track last start. Nicely in after Grima's claim. Should give a good account. AMALFI COAST (3) is on debut for Waterhouse/Bott. Best trial was the most recent at Warwick Farm. Half-brother to the five-time Group 1 winner Santa Ana Lane so he is bound to attract plenty of interest.
